_source.name: Sybrin AI
_source.description: Sybrin AI is an integrated technology stack powered by computer vision, machine learning, and data science designed to automate business processes. The solution integrates intelligent document processing, intelligent ID capture from documents and cards, and mobile document capture. Additionally, its liveness detection verifies that the person behind a remote interaction is a real person and is physically present through active or passive liveness detection using image processing techniques and neural networks to prevent spoof attacks.

features: Data parsing from platforms like Emails, Google Sheets, Webforms, CRM or any other application.
Integration with other business applications to extract real-time data.
Create custom mapping fields to get personalized data management and even lead generation.
_source.name: Email to Lead
_source.html: Email parser or Email to Lead is the productivity and automation tool that allows the user to extract information from email and store it into various formats including but not limited to Docs, Excel, CSV files, CRM software, etc. Businesses use this for creating leads automatically in their existing system.

_source.name: EdgeVerve XtractEdge (formerly Nia)
_source.description: With AI capabilities that use an ensemble of various Machine Learning and Deep Learning based techniques,  data management and analytics pipelines, XtractEdge Platform, from Infosys company EdgeVerve, structures world’s complex multi-document data, makes it consumption ready to unlock the latent business value.

_source.name: Intersect Labs
_source.description: Intersect Labs is a solution that lets users import data from any source, work with data in collaborative data notebooks, and share as interactive data app that anyone can run or schedule, from the company of the same name headquartered in San Diego.

_source.name: CData Sync
_source.description: CData's Sync is a data pipeline tool able to connect data sources to the user's database or data warehouse, supporting at present over 200 possible sources, and a range of destinations (e.g. Snowflake, S3, Redshift), connecting on-premise or SaaS sources and destinations.

_source.name: Docsumo
_source.description: Docsumo is document AI software with Intelligent OCR technology from the company in Singapore, that helps users convert unstructured documents such as pay stubs, invoices and bank statements to actionable data. Designed to work with documents in any format with minimal setup.

features: Extract structured data from paper documents
Low-code set up with user-friendly web portal
_source.name: FormX.ai
_source.html:
FormX.ai is an API that extracts structured information from physical documents. It aims to make data entry obsolete by understanding documents with the latest AI technology. The API can capture data from Receipts, Bank Statements, Identity Documents, Business cards, Forms, Licenses, and Certificates. Users can even train their Custom Models using the web portal.
Its clients range from Shopping Malls that want to extract product line items from receipts to recommend better offers to customers, to Private & Public Agencies who want to speed up the COVID-relief approval process by verifying address and name from bank statements automatically.
FormX is also available in private-cloud deployment.

_source.name: Veryfi
_source.description: Veryfi, headquartered in San Mateo, uses its Artificial Intelligence (AI)-based OCR API to provide Intelligent Document Processing and data extraction for a variety of purposes. Veryfi AI is pre-trained to extract and transform unstructured data from receipts, invoices, purchase orders, checks, W2s and other business documents into structured data, without a human in the loop. A solution for enterprises and technology companies alike, Veryfi’s AI-based platform boasts users among hundreds of organizations worldwide.

_source.name: Hypatos
_source.html:
Hypatos is designed to boost RPA projects for enterprises striving for backoffice automation and consulting projects that require document processing automation with AI.

Hypatos deep learning technology automates complex document based back-office processes, providing efficiency gains. Manual document processing is a major cost driver in organizations. Hypatos captures data points from documents, performs validations and automates processes, like accounting. The vendor states they serve the largest consumers of documents including 3 out of the Big 4 financial advisors and Shared Service Centers (SSCs) of large enterprises.

_source.name: FinCluez Data Hub
_source.description: FinCluez is a single data platform that addresses varied and complex data requirements across business areas, from Profinch, that helps banks to manage critical data effectively. FinCluez enables users to keep pace with changing customer needs and a continuously evolving regulatory climate.
_source.html:
FinCluez is a single data platform that addresses varied and complex data requirements across business areas, from Profinch, that helps banks to manage critical data effectively. FinCluez enables users to keep pace with changing customer needs and a continuously evolving regulatory climate.

FinCluez’s lightweight metadata driven engine takes care of extracting data from a wide range of source systems in the bank. It includes a scheduler component that enables automated extraction of data. The FinCluez Data Integration Layer is pre-integrated with FLEXCUBE Universal Banking Solution (from Oracle) with pre-defined metadata configurators.

FinCluez includes and features:
Prebuilt banking data lake.Insighting through thousands of OOB KPIs, metrics, interactive dashboards and operational reports across banking data marts.Use of industry standard banking data marts that support multi-dimensional reporting and analytics.Regulatory ready configurable frameworks.Built-in ELT tool, Scheduler.Data Traceability.

_source.name: MonocomSoft Advance Gmail Email Extractor
_source.html: Advance Gmail Email Extractor is a tool used to mine Email Ids from multiple Gmail accounts, boasting a fast and reliable data extracting process. To refine the extracted data the tool offers a built-in data filter feature.

_source.name: MonocomSoft Advance Files Email Extractor
_source.html: Advance Files Email Extractor is a tool used to extract Email Ids from Files like PDF, Doc, Docx, RTF, CSV, TXT, and more. The tool is equipped with advanced data filter option to refine the extracted data. The tool boasts a user-friendly interface and several features to make data extraction easier.

_source.name: MonocomSoft Web Phone and Email Extractor
_source.html: Web Phone and Email Extractor is used to parse Emails and Phone Numbers from a large number of online sources or websites. The software is able to fetch a large amount of data within a short time. To make the working easy and fast the tool comes with a build-in data filter to refine the data by multiple parameters. The list of Emails or Phone Numbers scraped by the tool can be saved in the form of CSV or TXT files.

_source.description: Amazing Hiring offers their candidate search engine and candidate profiles to prospective hirers and hirees, providing means of reviewing, contacting, and interacting with job prospects in data science, engineering, UX/UI, and other technical specialities.

features: Custom Data Extraction Models: Your business is unique – and so are your documents
Pre-Trained Data Extraction Models: For most commonly used documents
_source.name: Acodis – Intelligent Document Processing (IDP)
_source.html:
Acodis has been offering document data extraction since its founding in 2016. As every business process starts, finishes, or involves documents, Acodis Intelligent Document Processing platform can classify, extract, and automate them, in order to make data entry easier and faster.


The document automation tool aims to to meet all data requirements: whether a reliable PDF data extractor is needed, or an automated data entry program. Powered by machine learning, the AI data extraction process continuously evolves when it is fed more data. Users are not required to train the software; Acodis can manage this process for the user.

Benefits of data extraction with Acodis:
No complex rules/templates (continue working even if the document layout changes)
Scalable to all business processesData is never sent around the globe for verification Alternative 1: Manual Data Extraction
A human will look at a document, someone manually enters all relevant data points into an application and hits saveTime-consuming, error-prone, and expensive
Alternative 2: Rule-based OCR
Relies on a set of rules/templates to extract data from a documentCan break if a document format changes (a risk because documents constantly change)
Alternative 3: Standard Machine Learning
Demands a lot of time spent data labelling documentsIn the worst case, the supplier sends document to third parties for human verifications (likely not GDPR compliant)

_source.name: Ephesoft Transact
_source.description: Ephesoft in Irvine delivers Smart Capture technology on a private or public cloud platform designed to turn unstructured content into actionable information. From mortgage applications to invoices to insurance claims and beyond, the vendor states Ephesoft Transact makes quick work of processing so users can move faster. Ephesoft Transact uses supervised machine learning to automatically recognize different document types and layouts, then extract the relevant data from them. The vendor provides that their customers use Ephesoft Transact to automate document-based business processes, improving accuracy, increasing productivity and reducing costs.

_source.name: Bright Data
_source.description: Bright Data, headquartered in Tel Aviv and formerly under the name Luminati Networks, creates technologies to preserve a transparent internet, where anyone can access and collect public web data.
_source.html:
From data collection infrastructure to ready-made datasets, Bright Data allows the user to retrieve public web data. From finance, retail, and travel, to social media, cybersecurity, adtech, and more, market leaders are leveraging web data to maintain their advantage. Bright Data’s technology aims to provide a cost-effective way to perform fast and stable public web data collection at scale, converting unstructured data into structured data, to provide complete, accurate, and enriched datasets.

Bright Data's Data Collector is layered over the company's patented, peer network technology, with the ability to tap into difficult-to-access public websites. The Data Collector is available as a self-serve tool, or managed by Bright Data's own internal experts.

Alternately, the user can choose from hundreds of premade data collection templates, download already-collected datasets, or build a collector. Popular websites change their page structures regularly. The Bright Data Data Collector adapts to website structure changes and automatically retrieves data ready for analysis. Data Collector’s cloud infrastructure and data-as-a-service aim to make it easy to reliably collect accurate data at scale.

_source.name: Grepsr
_source.description: Grepsr is presented as a simple and streamlined data extraction platform from the company of the same name headquartered in New York, that helps bring and consume data to power applications and business processes – all without learning or configuring complex software tools. Grepsr helps with project setup to day-to-day maintenance of data sources and filters.
_source.html: Grepsr is a data extraction platform that helps users bring and consume data. Their enterprise web scraping solutions can sift through data to create meaningful insights. The technology scrapes thousands of webpages on a daily basis — overcoming all obstacles in the process — to find needed information. Grepsr then puts datasets through quality control protocols, and presents them cohesively in the form of APIs and spreadsheets.

_source.name: ABBYY Vantage
_source.description: ABBYY Vantage is a content intelligence tool designed to augment RPA and BPA applications by interpreting unstructured data in enterrpise content.
_source.html:
ABBYY Vantage is a comprehensive platform of cognitive services that applies AI to understand documents in a fast and simple way. Vantage aims to make today’s digital worker and processes smarter by delivering cognitive skills that read, understand, and extract insights from documents, helping enterprises accelerate digital transformation.

Features and BenefitsData extraction powered by AIBuilt with ABBYY’s OCR and machine learning technology, Vantage can identify documents and extract insights from them without using any pre-defined templates.Fast implementation and business resultsVantage no code / low code design approach enables business users to design, train, and deploy skills that handle the complexities of understanding content, without being a machine learning expert.Increased efficiency, reduced costDocument processing and data capture boasting exceptional accuracy and ongoing learning continuously improves straight-through-processing rates.
Accelerated digital transformationWith a number of available pre-trained skills, Vantage enables organizations to quickly expand their automation initiatives to additional business areas.
Extensible with the ABBYY MarketetplaceThe ABBYY Marketplace provides a collection of cognitive skills, connectors and assets, which enhance and extend the ABBYY Vantage platform to accelerate the digital transformation and automation initiatives of enterprises of any size, industry and geography. Skills developed both by ABBYY and by the ABBYY partner network cover various document types, use cases, languages and can be either fully trained and ready to go, or a framework, providing the basis for customers to adjust to specific requirements and train their own cognitive skills.

_source.name: ABBYY FlexiCapture
_source.description: ABBYY FlexiCapture is an Intelligent Document Processing platform that aims to bring together NLP, machine learning, and recognition capabilities into a single, enterprise-scale platform to handle every type of document, from simple forms to complex free-form documents, and every job size, from ad hoc single documents to large batch jobs requiring tough SLAs. Orchestrating the process from acquisition to delivery, FlexiCapture feeds content-driven business applications such as RPA and BPM, to help organizations focus on customer service, cost reduction, compliance, and competitive advantage.
_source.html:
ABBYY FlexiCapture is an Intelligent Document Processing platform that aims to bring together NLP, machine learning, and recognition capabilities into a single, enterprise-scale platform to handle every type of document, from simple forms to complex free-form documents, and every job size, from ad hoc single documents to large batch jobs requiring tough SLAs. Orchestrating the process from acquisition to delivery, FlexiCapture feeds content-driven business applications such as RPA and BPM, to help organizations focus on customer service, cost reduction, compliance, and competitive advantage.

An additional version, ABBYY FlexiCapture for Invoices, includes ready-to-go purchase order automation, and is designed to enable companies and organizations across the globe to increase the productivity of their AP processes out-of-the-box. Automate purchase order processing with the preconfigured project that contains the fields, rules, country settings, and validation rules required to capture data from purchase orders. Built on the same principles and technologies used for invoice processing, the solution provides out-of-the box extraction of main ﬁelds both in purchase orders and invoices.
